# ============================================================
# SOCIAL CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: social
scope: social.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for social.

## policy_rules
Social policy constrains:
- who may participate in which social spaces
- which social detail may be disclosed
- which interactions require restriction or review
- when social paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- participation scope must be explicit
- private/public scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public social summary
- participant-scoped detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- historical social detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow participation only for valid scope
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden entitlement through social presence
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If social context,
participation basis,
private/public scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the social path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- participation policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
- escalation rules are explicit
